  <!--tab layout-->

  <section class="section section-greencard__services">
    <Tabs>
    <div class="tab-wrapper">
      <nav class="tabammount_4 tab-sticky">
        <a href="#tab-1" class="flextabs__toggle tab-name align-middle active">Green Card</a>
        <a href="#tab-2" class="flextabs__toggle tab-name align-middle">Citizenship</a>
        <a href="#tab-3" class="flextabs__toggle tab-name align-middle">Visa</a>
        <a href="#tab-4" class="flextabs__toggle tab-name align-middle">Umra Package</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="all-tab-content-holder">
        <!--Tab 1 content  Start-->
        <div id="tab-1" class="tab-content-wrapper">
          <h3 class="heading__tab my-25">Green Card</h3>
          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            If you have recently become married to a U.S. citizen, you may be wondering if you
            can obtain citizenship yourself. First of all - congratulations! Our team at IRC is
            ready to help you and your spouse complete the journey of love and begin your lives
            together in the United States!
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            By obtaining a Green Card, the spouse of a current U.S. citizen can both live and
            work in any part of the United States of America. Once an individual obtains their
            Green Card, they will hold a &ldquo;permanent resident&rdquo; identification until
            the day they wish to apply for naturalization as a full U.S. citizen. The
            citizenship process can begin after three years.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            For many individuals, obtaining a Green Card is the natural way to start the journey
            of becoming a citizen. However, the process can be stressful and complicated. At
            IRC, our team of skilled immigration professionals can help you through every step,
            from filing your initial application to the finish line.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            The following are the different types of Green Card applications.
          </p>

          <ul class="green-card green-card--list my-35">
            <li>Adjustment Status (Green Card)</li>
            <li>Green Card Replacement</li>
            <li>Green Card Lottery</li>
            <li>VAWA: Violence Against Women Act</li>
          </ul>
          <!--button-->
          <a href="/green-card" class="btn btn--blue btn--animated">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!--Tab 1 content  End-->

        <!--Tab 2 content  Start-->
        <div id="tab-2" class="tab-content-wrapper">
          <h3 class="heading__tab my-25">Naturalization Applications</h3>
          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            Are you ready to become a naturalized U.S. citizen? The process may seem overwhelming
            and intimidating, but with the right help by your side, you can quickly and
            successfully complete your journey to full citizenship.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            In order to begin the naturalization process, you must complete the Application for
            Naturalization form - also known as Form N-400. This application begins the process
            for current Green Card holders to apply for full citizenship through the U.S.
            government. Before you begin - there are many eligibility requirements that must be
            met. IRC&rsquo;s team of trained immigration advisors stands ready to make sure that
            you have met all the requirements to be considered for naturalization.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            From filing the N-400 with U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) to
            completing the steps that meet the expectations of the Department of Homeland
            Security, IRC is ready to guide you step by step through the naturalization process.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            At an affordable cost, our team can help you complete your citizenship application,
            collect the necessary documents, and walk you through every step. Your American
            dream starts today!
          </p>

          <p class="my-10 tab-paragraph">
            The following are the application processes we can help you with.
          </p>

          <ul class="green-card green-card--list my-35">
            <li>Naturalization Adult</li>
            <li>Naturalization child applying under his/her parent</li>
            <li>Child Birth Abroad (Package)</li>
            <li>Medical Certification Disability Exemptions</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            Click <a class="tab-text-link" href="#">here to talk to an expert today.</a>
          </p>
          <a href="/citizenship" class="btn btn--blue btn--animated">Learn More</a>
        </div>

        <!--Tab 2 Content End-->

        <!--Tab 3 Content Start-->
        <div id="tab-3" class="tab-content-wrapper">
          <h3 class="heading__tab my-25">Visa Applications</h3>
          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            For many countries, the ability to quickly and effortlessly travel across
            international borders requires a current and valid visa. While the requirement of
            having a visa may seem simple, the process of obtaining one can be complicated and
            covered in red tape.
          </p>

          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            If you are beginning the process of applying for a visa, the team at IRC stands
            ready to help you each step of the way. From applications to processing, our team of
            skilled immigration experts can give you peace of mind while you prepare to travel.
            Our team can help you acquire a variety of visas, in the following categories:
          </p>

          <ul class="green-card green-card--list my-35">
            <li>
              Foreign Visas
              <ol class="green-card--inner my-15">
                <li>EU/Schengen</li>
                <li>UK</li>
                <li>Australia</li>
                <li>Ethiopia</li>
                <li>Kenya</li>
                <li>Uganda</li>
                <li>South Africa</li>
                <li>Saudi Arabia</li>
                <li>Zambia</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <ul class="green-card green-card--list my-35">
            <li>
              Immigration Visas
              <ol class="green-card--inner my-15">
                <li>Marriage visa</li>
                <li>Fiancé&rsquo;s Visa</li>
                <li>K1/3/4 expedited family reunion visas</li>
                <li>Tourist Visas B1/B2 or visitor visas</li>
                <li>Medical visa</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="my-35 tab-paragraph">
            Each visa is different and requires various applications and requirements to receive
            them. Depending on the country that you intend to travel to, or whether you are
            filing for family reunification visas, there may be extra requirements to fulfill
            along the way. The IRC team is ready to help you make the process simple and easy
            for you and your family.
          </p>
          <p class="my-20 tab-paragraph">
            Check out the full suite of online tools and resources from IRC as you begin your
            immigration process. When you are ready to get moving, we are ready to get you there!
          </p>
          <!--button-->
          <a href="/visa" class="btn btn--blue btn--animated">Learn More</a>
        </div>
        <!--Tab 3  Content End-->

        <!--Tab 4 Content Start-->
        <div id="tab-4" class="tab-content-wrapper">
          <h3 class="heading__tab my-25">Visa & Ticketing</h3>

          <p class="my-20 tab-paragraph">
            The Kingdom of Saudi Arabia is temporarily suspending Umra for citizens and
            residents in the kingdom due to the coronavirus outbreak, the Saudi Press Agency
            (SPA) reported on Wednesday.
          </p>
          <p class="my-20 tab-paragraph">
            The decision will be &ldquo;reviewed continuously&rdquo;, and the suspension will be
            lifted once the situation is under control, SPA quoted an official source at the
            ministry of Interior as saying.
          </p>
          <!--button-->
          <a
            href="https://gulfbusiness.com/saudi-temporarily-suspends-umrah-for-citizens-residents-over-coronavirus-outbreak-spa/"
            class="btn btn--blue btn--animated"
            target="_blank"
          >
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
        <!--Tab 4 Content End-->
      </div>
    </div>
    </Tabs>
  </section>

